A4.text: The Phoenix Park is a large public urban park in Dublin, Ireland, and in 1662 the newly appointed Viceroy, the Duke of Ormond, began converting the land surrounding Phoenix House into a 2,000‑acre (810 ha) hunting park.

A5.text: The Phoenix Park is a large public urban park in Dublin, Ireland, lying 2–4 kilometres west of the city centre, north of the River Liffey.
